01:15:03,120 --> 01:15:05,475
...l'll do a mailing of
Steven's greatest hits.

793
01:15:06,720 --> 01:15:08,199
I understand.

794
01:15:13,880 --> 01:15:16,075
Make fucking sure you do.

795
01:15:44,080 --> 01:15:45,559
Hey, Blondie!

796
01:15:45,920 --> 01:15:46,830
What are you doing here?

797
01:15:47,560 --> 01:15:48,356
Excuse me.

798
01:15:48,560 --> 01:15:50,915
I'm looking for apartment 209.

799
01:15:58,640 --> 01:15:59,868
This way?

800
01:16:01,440 --> 01:16:02,350
Thank you.

801
01:16:09,360 --> 01:16:10,793
There's a blonde coming up.

802
01:16:11,400 --> 01:16:12,355
Leave her alone.

803
01:16:13,280 --> 01:16:14,190
A blonde?

804
01:16:14,440 --> 01:16:15,634
Send her right up!

805
01:18:54,720 --> 01:18:57,109
That's not happiness
to see me, is it?

806
01:18:59,920 --> 01:19:01,239
Try surprise.

807
01:19:05,560 --> 01:19:09,519
The key to the dead man's
apartment was on my key chain.

808
01:19:10,680 --> 01:19:12,511
Someone put it there
after I killed him.

809
01:19:12,760 --> 01:19:16,150
Only one person in the world
could've done that.

810
01:19:17,120 --> 01:19:18,269
Me.

811
01:19:19,040 --> 01:19:20,234
Why?

812
01:19:20,680 --> 01:19:21,874
To protect you.

813
01:19:22,120 --> 01:19:23,439
From what?

814
01:19:25,800 --> 01:19:26,994
Your lover.

815
01:19:29,000 --> 01:19:32,276
Unless somebody else
sent these pictures.

816
01:19:51,640 --> 01:19:54,712
Amazing how you know people are in love,
even across the street.

817
01:19:55,360 --> 01:19:57,316
He called me here two months ago...

818
01:19:57,560 --> 01:20:00,199
...bragged about how
you'd fallen for him.

819
01:20:00,640 --> 01:20:02,870
I've shelled out over
$100,000 already...

820
01:20:03,160 --> 01:20:04,479
...but he wants a lot more.

821
01:20:04,960 --> 01:20:05,836
For what?

822
01:20:06,680 --> 01:20:08,318
For breaking it off.

823
01:20:10,240 --> 01:20:11,753
I don't believe you.

824
01:20:14,560 --> 01:20:16,039
Did he mention Belize?

825
01:20:19,120 --> 01:20:20,712
That's where he took
all the other ones.

826
01:20:22,480 --> 01:20:26,155
This guy was quite an aphrodisiac
for lonely women of means.

827
01:20:27,000 --> 01:20:29,560
He learned to paint in prison...

828
01:20:29,760 --> 01:20:31,193
...not at Berkeley.

829
01:20:46,360 --> 01:20:48,032
I don't know where we go from here.

830
01:20:48,280 --> 01:20:51,238
I don't even know if "we"
is an option.

831
01:20:51,840 --> 01:20:56,231
I have done everything in my power
to protect you from this...

832
01:20:56,480 --> 01:20:59,995
...career criminal that you've let
crawl into our bed.

833
01:21:01,040 --> 01:21:02,553
Why didn't you tell me?

834
01:21:04,280 --> 01:21:05,998
I was sure you were in love with him.

835
01:21:07,120 --> 01:21:08,439
Are you?

836
01:21:10,880 --> 01:21:12,996
I thought that I was.

837
01:21:15,800 --> 01:21:18,678
I can only imagine
what I've put you through.

838
01:21:25,160 --> 01:21:26,798
Is this why your business
is in trouble?

839
01:21:27,640 --> 01:21:28,789
Trouble?

840
01:21:29,520 --> 01:21:31,192
The banks, margin calls.

841
01:21:33,080 --> 01:21:36,311
How did you know...?
It hasn't helped, no.

842
01:21:37,560 --> 01:21:40,199
-But it's true, isn't it?
-Yes, it's true.

843
01:21:40,440 --> 01:21:42,351
But I can always make money.

844
01:21:42,600 --> 01:21:44,875
There's a goddamn sea of it out there.

845
01:21:45,200 --> 01:21:46,918
But there's only one of you.

846
01:21:48,600 --> 01:21:51,637
But why did you put his key
on my key chain?

847
01:21:54,560 --> 01:21:57,233
David threatened violence
from the very beginning.

848
01:21:57,560 --> 01:22:00,632
When I saw the body,
I was sure it was him.

849
01:22:01,480 --> 01:22:04,677
No doors had been forced open,
so I assumed that he had your key.

850
01:22:04,960 --> 01:22:07,076
But when? I'd used it
to come home that evening.

851
01:22:08,920 --> 01:22:12,356
Are you sure you used your key?
If memory serves me...

852
01:22:12,640 --> 01:22:16,076
...the door was wide open.
I saw you walk in.

853
01:22:16,320 --> 01:22:17,389
Maybe.

854
01:22:17,880 --> 01:22:20,758
In which case, he could've
taken your key anytime...

855
01:22:20,960 --> 01:22:25,033
...even the day before.
Did you see him the day before?

856
01:22:25,560 --> 01:22:26,595
Yes.

857
01:22:26,880 --> 01:22:30,839
I searched his pockets,
I found what I thought was your key...

858
01:22:31,040 --> 01:22:34,316
...I grabbed a screwdriver,
jimmied the door.

859
01:22:34,560 --> 01:22:37,233
I put it in his pocket,
took what I thought was your key...

860
01:22:37,800 --> 01:22:39,950
...and put it on your key chain.

861
01:22:40,720 --> 01:22:45,191
Baby, I am so sorry
for having to put you through this.

862
01:22:45,760 --> 01:22:47,910
It was the only thing I could do.

863
01:22:48,440 --> 01:22:50,112
Can you ever forgive me?

864
01:22:50,720 --> 01:22:52,790
Honey, I already have.

865
01:22:59,920 --> 01:23:02,115
We have to go to the police.

866
01:23:04,480 --> 01:23:07,790
I don't know if this is the time
for brutal honesty.

867
01:23:08,080 --> 01:23:09,672
I've tampered with evidence...

868
01:23:09,920 --> 01:23:11,239
...in a homicide.

869
01:23:11,480 --> 01:23:14,153
I paid off a blackmail.
I'm in over my head and so are you.

870
01:23:14,400 --> 01:23:18,313
Think it through!
David could say anything he wants.

871
01:23:18,560 --> 01:23:20,551
He could say that
I hired him to kill you.

872
01:23:20,960 --> 01:23:23,758
Or that he blackmailed us,
the happy, wealthy couple.

873
01:23:24,000 --> 01:23:26,434
It'd appear we killed that poor
bastard, thinking it was David.

874
01:23:26,680 --> 01:23:28,557
It depends on how he plays it.

875
01:23:28,800 --> 01:23:30,279
What about the man that I killed?

876
01:23:31,920 --> 01:23:33,273
That has to do with David?

877
01:23:33,520 --> 01:23:34,919
Well, it must!

878
01:23:35,320 --> 01:23:39,950
Do you have any idea how many
burglaries there are each day?

879
01:23:40,480 --> 01:23:41,993
I don't think so.

880
01:23:46,360 --> 01:23:47,873
What are we going to do now?

881
01:23:48,600 --> 01:23:52,559
We'll have to disentangle ourselves
from your artist friend.

882
01:23:54,160 --> 01:23:56,913
Is there anything in his loft that
could link David to us?

883
01:23:59,320 --> 01:24:00,753
My ring.

884
01:24:01,040 --> 01:24:02,678
You said it was being repaired.

885
01:24:03,960 --> 01:24:06,269
That was a lie.
I left it by the bed.

886
01:24:09,240 --> 01:24:10,275
Anything else?

887
01:24:11,160 --> 01:24:13,071
Isn't that enough?

888
01:24:15,520 --> 01:24:16,873
I'll get it.

889
01:24:33,560 --> 01:24:36,074
Will you be home when I get back?

890
01:24:36,720 --> 01:24:38,153
Yes.

891
01:25:47,760 --> 01:25:48,988
I'm on my way.

892
01:25:49,240 --> 01:25:51,913
I'm calling for Mr. David Shaw.

893
01:25:52,160 --> 01:25:53,673
Speaking.

894
01:25:53,920 --> 01:25:58,072
It's Truman Travel, confirming
your reservation for this afternoon.

895
01:25:58,360 --> 01:25:59,588
Thank you.

896
01:26:19,080 --> 01:26:20,069
Excuse me, sir.

897
01:26:20,400 --> 01:26:21,958
Could you spare 400 grand?

898
01:26:22,240 --> 01:26:23,912
I don't see why not.

899
01:26:29,560 --> 01:26:31,516
Don't think I won't count it.

900
01:26:31,720 --> 01:26:33,039
Naturally.

901
01:26:35,680 --> 01:26:38,194
Think of that
as your commemorative copy.

902
01:26:46,120 --> 01:26:48,509
Nice doing business with you, Steve.

903
01:26:53,240 --> 01:26:54,434
You take care.

904
01:28:10,040 --> 01:28:13,396
Last call: boarding
train number 32 for Montreal...

905
01:28:13,640 --> 01:28:16,074
...departing on track number 16.
All aboard.

906
01:28:24,600 --> 01:28:25,669
Right this way.

907
01:28:33,200 --> 01:28:34,713
Here we are, sir.

908
01:28:38,120 --> 01:28:39,473
Thank you, sir.

909
01:29:21,440 --> 01:29:24,079
Wanted to let you know
the dining car opens at 7.

910
01:29:24,360 --> 01:29:25,873
Closes at 10 sharp.

911
01:29:33,440 --> 01:29:35,271
Okay, everything's fine.

912
01:29:48,640 --> 01:29:50,232
Attention, please.

913
01:29:50,520 --> 01:29:55,310
Last call for train 32
departing to Montreal in 4 minutes.

914
01:30:07,560 --> 01:30:09,949
How's that for wet work?

915
01:30:13,320 --> 01:30:15,038
You should thank me.

916
01:30:15,320 --> 01:30:18,710
Artists are always appreciated
more after they're dead.

917
01:30:26,800 --> 01:30:28,028
You lose.

918
01:30:28,960 --> 01:30:31,235
I'm sorry, you got to speak up.
I can't hear you.

919
01:30:32,400 --> 01:30:33,389
You're dying.

920
01:30:40,880 --> 01:30:41,630
Steven's...

921
01:30:41,960 --> 01:30:43,518
...greatest hits.

922
01:31:09,480 --> 01:31:11,516
Excuse me.
I got an emergency here.

923
01:31:11,760 --> 01:31:12,590
What are you doing?

924
01:31:12,880 --> 01:31:15,269
-This'll make it easier.
-Be my guest!

925
01:31:16,200 --> 01:31:17,758
91st and Fifth.

926
01:31:26,160 --> 01:31:28,390
Has there been a delivery today?

927
01:31:28,600 --> 01:31:32,479
Just one. It came by messenger,
Your wife took it up with the mail.

928
01:32:52,640 --> 01:32:53,789
I didn't know you were here.

929
01:32:54,240 --> 01:32:55,958
I was out on the terrace.

930
01:33:09,200 --> 01:33:10,918
Welcome home.

931
01:33:17,560 --> 01:33:19,949
It's time for a new start.

932
01:33:21,920 --> 01:33:25,435
What do you say we go out
for dinner this evening?

933
01:33:25,720 --> 01:33:28,712
Just the two of us,
someplace quiet...

934
01:33:29,200 --> 01:33:30,792
...in the neighborhood.

935
01:33:31,280 --> 01:33:32,315
Like that?

936
01:33:34,320 --> 01:33:36,754
I'll be right back.
I'm going to clean up.

937
01:35:12,640 --> 01:35:13,390
Honey?

938
01:35:15,120 --> 01:35:18,590
Let's stay home tonight.
I'll go pick up something to eat.

939
01:35:21,200 --> 01:35:23,873
That's sweet of you.
Just don't be too long.

940
01:35:24,440 --> 01:35:25,429
I won't.

941
01:35:27,920 --> 01:35:31,515
Before I forget, I think
we should have the locks changed.

942
01:35:39,800 --> 01:35:40,755
Why?

943
01:35:41,480 --> 01:35:43,789
Because I still can't find my key.

944
01:35:47,560 --> 01:35:50,916
Good idea. I'll call
the locksmith in the morning.

945
01:35:51,360 --> 01:35:53,316
Better be safe than sorry.

946
01:35:53,600 --> 01:35:54,794
Thanks.

947
01:35:56,320 --> 01:35:58,276
See you soon. Hurry back.

948
01:36:34,120 --> 01:36:36,111
Must have put it back on his way in.

949
01:36:37,560 --> 01:36:39,551
Didn't plan on that, did you?

950
01:36:47,120 --> 01:36:48,473
Young David...

951
01:36:49,520 --> 01:36:51,078
...he was very unpredictable.

952
01:36:51,920 --> 01:36:53,797
Maybe you'll share a cell.

953
01:36:55,200 --> 01:36:56,428
Why?

954
01:36:57,200 --> 01:36:58,599
Because of this?

955
01:37:00,920 --> 01:37:02,990
I just found the key you lost.

956
01:37:03,320 --> 01:37:04,958
You left it for him.

957
01:37:06,040 --> 01:37:07,234
You mean the man you killed.

958
01:37:07,480 --> 01:37:09,630
-I never met the gentleman.
-David did.

959
01:37:09,880 --> 01:37:12,189
They'll have a hard time
proving I knew David.

960
01:37:12,480 --> 01:37:14,630
The blackmail proves it.

961
01:37:14,840 --> 01:37:15,875
What blackmail?

962
01:37:16,480 --> 01:37:17,754
There's only one letter...

963
01:37:18,000 --> 01:37:19,911
...and I'm afraid that's vanished.

964
01:37:21,760 --> 01:37:24,228
The thing is, we're just
another married couple...

965
01:37:24,480 --> 01:37:26,391
...trying to work things out.

966
01:37:27,320 --> 01:37:28,469
Work it out?

967
01:37:29,600 --> 01:37:30,874
Work it out?

968
01:37:32,680 --> 01:37:35,558
Because that's what she does
on nights that I play cards.

969
01:37:35,840 --> 01:37:37,956
Like the combination to the safe?

970
01:37:38,240 --> 01:37:39,514
It's our wedding day, Steven.

971
01:37:41,040 --> 01:37:44,555
You work it out on your fucking own!
This is over!

972
01:37:49,520 --> 01:37:51,670
I'll tell you when it's over.

973
01:38:11,720 --> 01:38:14,154
The only way you leave me
is dead.

974
01:39:10,960 --> 01:39:15,670
I always thought that "bludgeon"
had a spur-of-the-moment sound.

975
01:39:16,720 --> 01:39:19,234
Maybe you could use one of these.

976
01:39:21,600 --> 01:39:23,989
Rifle the jewelry in the bedroom.

977
01:39:24,280 --> 01:39:27,670
Disable the service entrance lock.
Make it look like it was jimmied.

978
01:39:28,160 --> 01:39:29,718
Put the key back under the pipe...

979
01:39:29,960 --> 01:39:31,951
...then leave
the same way you came in.

980
01:39:33,160 --> 01:39:35,720
And what happens
if the plan goes to hell?

981
01:39:37,840 --> 01:39:39,239
It won't.

982
01:39:49,520 --> 01:39:51,238
He said he was going to kill me.

983
01:39:52,240 --> 01:39:54,037
So I tried to run.

984
01:39:55,040 --> 01:39:56,632
And then he attacked you?

985
01:39:59,480 --> 01:40:00,595
Yes.

986
01:40:03,600 --> 01:40:05,352
What else could you do?

987
01:40:11,640 --> 01:40:14,473
May God be with you.

988
01:40:15,440 --> 01:40:17,476
And you as well.



